{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Fg2oF6HdFHJ5cxyCxCS2wb","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a comprehensive view. Let me compile my findings into a clear report.\n\n## Summary: Bankrun Test Setup & Local Validator Configuration\n\nBased on my analysis of the codebase, here's how the project handles local validator setup and bankrun testing:\n\n### 1. **Bankrun Setup in Tests**\n\nBoth test files (`coinflip.ts` and `platform.ts`) use **bankrun with anchor-bankrun** for in-process testing:\n\n**Key Pattern** (from `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/tests/coinflip.ts:132-149`):\n```typescript\nconst context = await startAnchor(\"./\", [], [\n  { address: opponent.publicKey, info: fundedAccountData() },\n  // ... more accounts\n]);\n\nconst creatorProvider = new BankrunProvider(context);\nconst creatorProgram = new Program<Coinflip>(IDL, creatorProvider);\n```\n\n- Uses `startAnchor()` from `anchor-bankrun` to create an isolated bankrun context\n- No external validator or deployment required\n- Programs are loaded from compiled IDLs in `solana/target/idl/`\n- Mock accounts are injected directly via `startAnchor()` second argument\n\n### 2. **Test Execution Command**\n\n**From `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/Anchor.toml:24`:**\n```toml\n[scripts]\ntest = \"pnpm exec mocha --require tsx/cjs -t 1000000 tests/**/*.ts\"\n```\n\n**From `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/package.json:6`:**\n```json\n\"test\": \"anchor test --skip-local-validator --skip-deploy\"\n```\n\n**Critical Flags** (from `/workspaces/rng-utopia/scripts/verify:91`):\n```bash\nanchor test --skip-local-validator --skip-deploy\n```\n\nThese flags tell Anchor CLI to:\n- **`--skip-local-validator`**: Do NOT start `solana-test-validator` (bankrun handles it in-process)\n- **`--skip-deploy`**: Do NOT deploy programs (bankrun provides them already loaded from IDLs)\n\n### 3. **Binary Availability**\n\n`solana-test-validator` **is available** on the system:\n```\n/home/vscode/.local/share/solana/install/active_release/bin/solana-test-validator\n```\n\nBut it's **not used for unit/integration tests** — only for E2E tests (see below).\n\n### 4. **Frontend RPC Configuration**\n\n**For development/E2E tests** (`/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/playwright.local.config.ts:40-44`):\n```typescript\nwebServer: {\n  env: {\n    VITE_MOCK_MODE: \"false\",\n    VITE_RPC_URL: \"http://127.0.0.1:8899\",\n    VITE_SOLANA_NETWORK: \"localnet\",\n  },\n}\n```\n\nThe E2E tests expect a real `solana-test-validator` running on `8899` (standard localnet port), but that's **outside the scope of unit/integration anchor tests**.\n\n**For normal dev mode** (`/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/packages/wallet/src/WalletProvider.tsx:16-25`):\n```typescript\nconst DEFAULT_RPC_URL = \"https://api.devnet.solana.com\";\nconst envUrl = () =>\n  import.meta.env?.VITE_RPC_URL\n    ? import.meta.env.VITE_RPC_URL\n    : DEFAULT_RPC_URL;\n```\n\n### 5. **Verification Script Flow**\n\n**From `/workspaces/rng-utopia/scripts/verify` (lines 87-91)**:\n1. Runs TypeScript/lint/typecheck/build via pnpm\n2. Then runs anchor tests:\n   ```bash\n   cd sources/rng-utopia/solana\n   anchor test --skip-local-validator --skip-deploy\n   ```\n3. This invokes mocha with the test script from `Anchor.toml`\n\n### 6. **Project Structure**\n\n- **Test files**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/tests/*.ts`\n- **IDL outputs** (required by tests): `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/target/idl/*.json`\n- **Programs**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/programs/coinflip/` and `/solana/programs/platform/`\n\n### Key Takeaway\n\nThe project uses **bankrun for fast, isolated unit/integration tests** (no validator process) and **reserves solana-test-validator for E2E tests only** (which require a running chain with the actual webapp). The verify script runs only bankrun tests because they're deterministic and don't require external processes."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a1eba1705b0c744cf (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 66588\ntool_uses: 16\nduration_ms: 85044</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"faf1a871-f71a-4e6b-a898-077ce425db1a","uuid":"e636fe2d-ba13-4ef4-bcd9-c64be93acf8e","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Check how the existing bankrun/anchor tests handle the local validator. Look at:\n\n1. `sources/rng-utopia/solana/tests/coinflip.ts` — how does bankrun set up programs?\n2. Any global setup files in `sources/rng-utopia/solana/tests/`\n3. Check if `solana-test-validator` binary is available: run `which solana-test-validator` or look for references to it\n\nAlso check:\n4. The root `scripts/` directory for any existing verify or test scripts\n5. `sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/vite.config.ts` for how VITE_RPC_URL is configured\n\nBase path: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/`","agentId":"a1eba1705b0c744cf","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a comprehensive view. Let me compile my findings into a clear report.\n\n## Summary: Bankrun Test Setup & Local Validator Configuration\n\nBased on my analysis of the codebase, here's how the project handles local validator setup and bankrun testing:\n\n### 1. **Bankrun Setup in Tests**\n\nBoth test files (`coinflip.ts` and `platform.ts`) use **bankrun with anchor-bankrun** for in-process testing:\n\n**Key Pattern** (from `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/tests/coinflip.ts:132-149`):\n```typescript\nconst context = await startAnchor(\"./\", [], [\n  { address: opponent.publicKey, info: fundedAccountData() },\n  // ... more accounts\n]);\n\nconst creatorProvider = new BankrunProvider(context);\nconst creatorProgram = new Program<Coinflip>(IDL, creatorProvider);\n```\n\n- Uses `startAnchor()` from `anchor-bankrun` to create an isolated bankrun conte